<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-17-0013 </DOCNO><TEXT>The book investigates the subject-related adequacy of scientific and judicialdecisions in the court proceeding, and their feasibility. Also, the socialcontext of more and more having recourse to science and technology isbrought to the foreground. The problems and questions thus made visibleare discussed by analysing the provisions of the Atomic Energy Act andthe practice adopted by the courts in matters of nuclear licensing. (orig./HSCH).</TEXT></DOC>